'''Braian Óscar Ojeda Rodríguez''' (born 27 June 2000) is a Paraguayan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]] for [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]] and the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]].<ref name="Soccerway">{{Soccerway|braian-ojeda/475440}}</ref>

Ojeda graduated from the academy of [[Club Olimpia|Olimpia]] in 2018, with whom he helped win that year's [[2018 APF División de Honor#Torneo Clausura|Clausura]], before joining [[Defensa y Justicia]] the following year on loan. After his return, Ojeda joined [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] in 2021, but only made three appearances with them before joining [[Real Salt Lake]] on loan the following year. In mid-2023, Ojeda joined Real Salt Lake on a permanent deal. In 2026, Ojeda joined fellow Major League Soccer side Orlando City.

Ojeda represented Paraguay at the [[Paraguay national under-17 football team|U17]], [[Paraguay national under-20 football team|U20]], and [[Paraguay national under-23 football team|U23]] levels, before representing the senior team in 2021. With Paraguay, Ojeda has played at the [[2021 Copa América]] and will represent the nation at the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].

==Club career==
Ojeda began his career with [[Paraguayan Primera División]] team [[Club Olimpia|Olimpia]].<ref name="Soccerway"/> He was promoted into senior football at the end of the [[2018 Paraguayan Primera División season|2018]] campaign, appearing for his professional debut on 2 December in a 3–2 victory over [[Club Sol de América|Sol de América]]; he was substituted off at half-time.<ref name="Soccerway"/> Another appearances followed a week later against [[Club Atlético 3 de Febrero|3 de Febrero]], as Olimpia received their forty-second league title.<ref name="Soccerway"/> He also participated in three [[Copa Paraguay]] games that year.<ref name="OLI1">{{cite news |title=Braian Ojeda – Club Olimpia |url=https://clubolimpia.com.py/jugador/braian-ojeda/ |accessdate=13 July 2019 |work=Olimpia|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190713070428/https://clubolimpia.com.py/jugador/braian-ojeda/|archive-date=13 July 2019}}</ref><ref name="ABC1">{{cite news |title=Braian Ojeda, otra buena aparición |url=https://www.abc.com.py/deportes/futbol/braian-ojeda-otra-buena-aparicion-1761520.html |accessdate=13 July 2019 |work=ABC |date=21 November 2018}}</ref> In March 2019, Ojeda renewed his contract.<ref name="TS1">{{cite news |title=Nicolás Morínigo renueva contrato con Olimpia |url=http://www.tigosports.com.py/futbol/nicolas-morinigo-renueva-contrato-con-olimpia |accessdate=13 July 2019 |work=Tigo Sports |date=26 March 2019}}</ref><ref name="VER1">{{cite news |title=El juvenil de Olimpia que podría ir a Europa |url=https://www.versus.com.py/2019/06/11/el-juvenil-de-olimpia-que-podria-ir-a-europa/ |accessdate=13 July 2019 |work=Versus |date=11 June 2019}}</ref> In July, after not featuring in [[2019 Paraguayan Primera División season|2019]], Ojeda was loaned out to [[Defensa y Justicia]] of the [[Argentine Primera División]].<ref name="DYJ1">{{cite news |title=Sangre Guaraní para Defensa |url=http://www.defensayjusticia.org.ar/noticias/1139 |accessdate=13 July 2019 |work=Defensa y Justicia |date=12 July 2019|archive-date=4 September 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210904154048/http://www.defensayjusticia.org.ar/noticias/1139|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="TYC1">{{cite news |title=Defensa y Justicia: Braian Ojeda, la apuesta del halcón |url=https://www.tycsports.com/superliga/defensa-y-justicia-braian-ojeda-la-apuesta-del-halcon-20190712.html |accessdate=13 July 2019 |work=TyC Sports |date=12 July 2019}}</ref>

On 31 August 2021, Ojeda moved to [[EFL Championship]] side [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] on a four-year deal for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nottinghamforest.co.uk/news/2021/august/Two-more-signings-as-Ojeda-checks-in/ |title=Two more signings as Ojeda checks in |date=31 August 2021}}</ref> He made his debut in a goalless draw against [[Luton Town]] on 23 November 2021.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59300704 |title=Nottingham Forest 0-0 Luton |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=23 November 2021 |access-date=8 February 2022}}</ref>

On 4 August 2022, Ojeda was loaned to [[Major League Soccer]] (MLS) side [[Real Salt Lake]] for the 2022–23 season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ojeda Departs on Loan |url=https://www.nottinghamforest.co.uk/news/2022/august/04/ojeda-departs-on-loan/ |publisher=Nottingham Forest F.C. |date=4 August 2022}}</ref> On 1 August 2023, the deal was made permanent and Ojeda joined Salt Lake on a permanent transfer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nottinghamforest.co.uk/news/2023/august/01/ojeda-departs/ |title=Ojeda departs |date=August 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rsl.com/news/real-salt-lake-permanently-acquires-paraguayan-international-braian-ojeda-from-n |title=Real Salt Lake Permanently Acquires Paraguayan International Braian Ojeda from Nottingham Forest &#124; Real Salt Lake}}</ref>

On 2 January 2026, Ojeda signed with fellow MLS team [[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]] on a four-season contract in exchange for [[United States dollar|$]]1.3 million in general allocation money split across two seasons.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Gramajo |first=Mike |date=2 January 2026 |title=Orlando City signs Braian Ojeda following trade with Real Salt Lake |url=https://www.wesh.com/article/orlando-city-signs-braian-ojeda-trade-real-salt-lake/69904305 |access-date=2 January 2026 |work=[[WESH]]}}</ref> Ojeda made his debut for Orlando City in the team's season-opening match on 21 February as Orlando lost 2–1 to the [[New York Red Bulls]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=ORLvsRBNY 02-21-2026 |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/competitions/mls-regular-season/2026/matches/orlvsrbny-02-21-2026/ |access-date=21 February 2026 |website=[[Major League Soccer]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=22 February 2026 |title=Match report: Orlando City SC drops season opener Against Red Bull New York |url=https://www.orlandocitysc.com/news/match-report-orlando-city-sc-drops-season-opener-against-red-bull-new-york|access-date=22 February 2026 |website=[[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]]}}</ref> On 19 May, Ojeda made two assists in a 4–1 win over [[Atlanta United FC|Atlanta United]] in the [[2026 U.S. Open Cup#Quarterfinals|quarter-finals of the U.S. Open Cup]], helping to advance Orlando City to their first semi-finals since [[2022 U.S. Open Cup|2022]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Foley |first=Kyle |date=19 May 2026 |title=Orlando City jumps out to early lead vs. Atlanta, cruises to U.S. Open Cup semifinal |url=https://www.orlandosentinel.com/2026/05/19/orlando-city-jumps-out-to-early-lead-vs-atlanta-cruises-to-u-s-open-cup-semifinal/ |access-date=20 May 2026 |work=[[Orlando Sentinel]]}}</ref>

==International career==
Ojeda represented Paraguay at [[Paraguay men's national under-17 football team|U17]] and [[Paraguay men's national under-20 football team|U20]] level.<ref name="Soccerway"/> He appeared eight times at the [[2017 South American U-17 Championship]] in Chile, as they qualified for the [[2017 FIFA U-17 World Cup]] in India; where he featured against [[Mali national under-17 football team|Mali]], [[New Zealand national under-17 football team|New Zealand]] and the [[United States men's national under-17 soccer team|United States]].<ref name="Soccerway"/><ref name="CON1">{{cite news |title=Paraguai Sub-17 termina o ano com treinos no Albiróga |url=http://www.conmebol.com/pt-br/paraguai-sub-17-termina-o-ano-com-treinos-no-albiroga |accessdate=13 July 2019 |work=CONMEBOL |date=27 December 2016}}</ref><ref name="GOA1">{{cite news |title=Under-17 World Cup: Paraguay announce 24-member squad |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/under-17-world-cup-paraguay-announce-24-member-squad/2nzrcsfbfg1r1wrbzhbhil6y8 |accessdate=13 July 2019 |work=Goal |date=14 September 2017}}</ref> In 2019, Ojeda played three times at the [[2019 South American U-20 Championship|South American U-20 Championship]].<ref name="Soccerway"/><ref name="CRO1">{{cite news |title=Ya están los 23 para el Sudamericano Sub 20 |url=http://www.cronica.com.py/2018/12/22/ya-estan-los-23-sudamericano-sub-20/ |accessdate=13 July 2019 |work=Crónica |date=22 December 2018}}</ref>

In 2020, Ojeda held representative honours with the Paraguay national under-23 squad at the [[2020 CONMEBOL Pre-Olympic Tournament]].

He made his debut for the [[Paraguay national football team|senior squad]] on 2 September 2021 in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]], a 2–0 away loss. He substituted [[Hugo Martínez (footballer)|Hugo Martínez]] in the 65th-minute.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=[[FIFA]] |url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/mens/worldcup/qatar2022/qualifiers/conmebol/match-center/400104608 |title=Ecuador v Paraguay game report |date=2 September 2021}}</ref>

On 1 June 2026, it was announced that Paraguay head coach [[Gustavo Alfaro]] had selected Ojeda for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Dorff |first=Marcel |date=1 June 2026 |title=Paraguay Announces Squad for 2026 FIFA World Cup |url=https://heavy.com/sports/soccer/world-cup/paraguay-announces-squad-fifa-world-cup/ |access-date=1 June 2026 |work=[[Heavy (website)|Heavy]]}}</ref>

